: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md`\n73: - Proposal: `changes/AR-031/proposal.md`\n74: - Tasks: `changes/AR-031/tasks.md`\n75: - [TO BE FILLED: Add relevant references]\n\n(End of file - total 75 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031 ŌĆö RBAC ķģŹńĮ« Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-031 ŌĆö RBAC ķģŹńĮ« |\n| Module | `manifests` |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Describe the RBAC configuration design]\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/design.md","time":{"start":1775884934183,"end":1775884934216}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884934219,"sessionID":"ses_28502a6edffemTCed1yGL8nzbj","part":{"id":"prt_d7afd90e6001iUpC4Xt3tLO3zs","messageID":"msg_d7afd7259001PiJCuntT0qmuxP","sessionID":"ses_28502a6edffemTCed1yGL8nzbj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-95feb8d198994173abaad92c2f660795","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-031 ŌĆö RBAC ķģŹńĮ« (SA/Role/Binding)\n2: \n3: ## µ”éĶ┐░\n4: \n5: | Õ▒×µĆ¦ | ÕĆ╝ |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-031 |\n8: | Module | manifests |\n9: | Language | YAML |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (ńø«ńÜä)\n15: \n16: Define Kubernetes RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding) for AgentCube components to enable secure, least-privilege access to Kubernetes API resources. This proposal:\n17: \n18: 1. **Router RBAC**: Namespace-scoped Role for Secret management (JWT signing keys, identity secrets)\n19: 2. **WorkloadManager RBAC**: Cluster-wide ClusterRole for sandbox lifecycle management, CRD operations, and Pod/Secret access\n20: 3. **Helm Templating**: Parameterized RBAC creation via values.yaml flags (e.g., `router.rbac.create`)\n21: 4. **Security Compliance**: Follow Kubernetes RBAC best practices with minimal permission grants\n22: \n23: **RBAC Components**:\n24: \n25: | Component | Scope | Purpose |\n26: |-----------|-------|---------|\n27: | `router` | Namespace (Role) | Manage Secrets for session JWT signing and identity |\n28: | `workloadmanager` | Cluster (ClusterRole) | Create/manage Sandboxes, CodeInterpreters, AgentRuntimes, Pods, Secrets, TokenReviews |\n29: \n30: ---\n31: \n32: ## 2. Scope (ĶīāÕø┤)\n33: \n34: ### 2.1 In Scope\n35: \n36: | Deliverable | Description |\n37: |-------------|-------------|\n38: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding for Router (namespace-scoped) |\n39: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding for WorkloadManager |\n40: | `values.yaml` RBAC flags | `router.rbac.create`, `router.serviceAccountName` configuration options |\n41: | RBAC validation | Ensure minimal permissions per component |\n42: \n43: ### 2.2 RBAC Permission Matrix\n44: \n45: **Router Role (Namespace-scoped)**:\n46: \n47: | apiGroups | Resources | Verbs |\n48: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n49: | `\"\"` (core) | secrets | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete |\n50: \n51: **WorkloadManager ClusterRole**:\n52: \n53: | apiGroups | Resources | Verbs |\n54: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n55: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | sandboxes | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete |\n56: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | sandboxclaims, sandboxtemplates, sandboxwarmpools | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete |\n57: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | sandboxwarmpools/status | get, update, patch |\n58: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | codeinterpreters | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete |\n59: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | codeinterpreters/status, codeinterpreters/finalizers | get, update, patch |\n60: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | agentruntimes | get, list, watch |\n61: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | agentruntimes/status | update, patch |\n62: | `\"\"` (core) | pods | get, list, watch |\n63: | `\"\"` (core) | secrets | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete |\n64: | `authentication.k8s.io` | tokenreviews | create |\n65: \n66: ### 2.3 Out of Scope\n67: \n68: | Item | Reason |\n69: |------|--------|\n70: | Volcano scheduler RBAC | Separate component with its own RBAC in volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml |\n71: | User-facing RBAC | Users interact via Router; no direct K8s API access required |\n72: | NetworkPolicy | Environment-specific; not in base chart |\n73: | PodSecurityPolicy | Deprecated in K8s 1.25+; use PodSecurity Standards instead |\n74: | Custom role aggregation | Single Role/ClusterRole per component sufficient |\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: ## 3. Impact Analysis (ÕĮ▒ÕōŹÕłåµ×É)\n79: \n80: ### 3.1 µ¢░Õó×µ¢ćõ╗Č\n81: \n82: | File | Description |\n83: |------|-------------|\n84: | N/A | RBAC templates already exist; this AR documents and validates them |\n85: \n86: ### 3.2 õ┐«µö╣µ¢ćõ╗Č\n87: \n88: | File | Change |\n89: |------|--------|\n90: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Add validation guard for serviceAccountName requirement |\n91: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Document `router.rbac.create` and `router.serviceAccountName` defaults |\n92: \n93: ### 3.3 Upstream Dependencies\n94: \n95: | Dependency | Purpose |\n96: |------------|---------|\n97: | `Kubernetes 1.24+` | RBAC API stability (rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1) |\n98: | `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox CRDs` | Sandboxes, SandboxClaims, SandboxTemplates, SandboxWarmPools resources |\n99: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh CRDs` | CodeInterpreters, AgentRuntimes custom resources |\n100: \n101: ### 3.4 Downstream Consumers\n102: \n103: | Consumer | Usage |\n104: |----------|-------|\n105: | `Router Deployment` | Uses ServiceAccount for Pod identity; mounts secrets |\n106: | `WorkloadManager Deployment` | Uses ServiceAccount for sandbox/CRD operations |\n107: | `E2E Tests (run_e2e.sh)` | Helm install with RBAC enabled validates permission grants |\n108: | `Production deployments` | RBAC required for cluster access; audit logging for permission usage |\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (ÕżćķĆēµ¢╣µĪł)\n113: \n114: ### Alternative 1: ClusterRole for Router (cluster-wide permissions)\n115: \n116: **Approach**: Grant Router cluster-wide ClusterRole for Secret access across namespaces.\n117: \n118: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n119: |--------|------------|\n120: | Pros | Single binding; access secrets in any namespace |\n121: | Cons | Over-permissive; Router only needs secrets in its own namespace |\n122: \n123: **Decision**: Rejected. Router operates within single namespace (JWT secrets, identity secrets). Namespace-scoped Role provides better security isolation.\n124: \n125: ### Alternative 2: Pre-defined ServiceAccount (no RBAC creation)\n126: \n127: **Approach**: Require pre-existing ServiceAccount and RBAC; Helm chart only references them.\n128: \n129: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n130: |--------|------------|\n131: | Pros | Separates RBAC management from deployment; supports external IAM |\n132: | Cons | Additional manual setup; deployment fails if SA missing; no self-contained install |\n133: \n134: **Decision**: Rejected as default. `router.rbac.create=false` option allows this pattern for environments with external RBAC management, but default is self-contained RBAC creation.\n135: \n136: ### Alternative 3: RoleBinding for WorkloadManager (namespace-scoped)\n137: \n138: **Approach**: Use namespace-scoped Role instead of ClusterRole for WorkloadManager.\n139: \n140: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n141: |--------|------------|\n142: | Pros | Narrower permission scope; namespace isolation |\n143: | Cons | WorkloadManager must access agent-sandbox CRDs (cluster-scoped) and manage sandboxes across namespaces |\n144: \n145: **Decision**: Rejected. Agent-sandbox CRDs (Sandboxes, SandboxClaims) are cluster-scoped resources. ClusterRole is required for cross-namespace operations.\n146: \n147: ### Alternative 4: Aggregated ClusterRoles\n148: \n149: **Approach**: Use ClusterRole aggregation to compose permissions from multiple smaller ClusterRoles.\n150: \n151: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n152: |--------|------------|\n153: | Pros | Reusable permission sets; granular control; easier audits |\n154: | Cons | Additional complexity; multiple ClusterRole objects; overkill for single-component permissions |\n155: \n156: **Decision**: Rejected. Single ClusterRole per component is simpler and sufficient. Aggregation useful for multi-component shared permissions; not needed for current scope.\n157: \n158: ### Alternative 5: Static RBAC YAML (no Helm templating)\n159: \n160: **Approach**: Provide static RBAC YAML files without Helm conditionals.\n161: \n162: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n163: |--------|------------|\n164: | Pros | Simpler; no template logic; deterministic output |\n165: | Cons | Cannot disable RBAC per deployment; cannot customize ServiceAccount names; all-or-nothing install |\n166: \n167: **Decision**: Rejected. Helm templating with `rbac.create` flag enables flexible deployment (external RBAC management, custom SA names).\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## 5. Risks\n172: \n173: | Risk | Mitigation |\n174: |------|------------|\n175: | ClusterRole over-permissive | Audit permissions annually; only grant verbs needed for operation; no wildcard resources |\n176: | ServiceAccount name collision | `router.serviceAccountName` configurable via values; default namespaced naming |\n177: | Missing RBAC during install | Helm template guard: `{{- fail \"router.serviceAccountName must be set\" }}` when RBAC enabled but SA missing |\n178: | TokenReview permission leak | Only granted to WorkloadManager; Router has no TokenReview access |\n179: | CRD version mismatch | RBAC verbs stable across CRD versions; no version-specific permissions |\n180: | Namespace isolation breach | Router Role limited to single namespace; cannot access secrets in other namespaces |\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n185: \n186: - [ ] Validate `rbac-router.yaml` template renders correctly with `helm template`\n187: - [ ] Validate `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` template renders correctly\n188: - [ ] Verify Router Role only grants Secret permissions (no Pod/CRD access)\n189: - [ ] Verify WorkloadManager ClusterRole grants minimal required verbs\n190: - [ ] Test RBAC conditional: `router.rbac.create=false` skips RBAC creation\n191: - [ ] Test guard: `router.rbac.create=true` without `serviceAccountName` fails template\n192: - [ ] Validate ServiceAccount appears in Deployment spec when RBAC enabled\n193: - [ ] E2E test: WorkloadManager can create/manage sandboxes\n194: - [ ] E2E test: Router can read/write secrets in its namespace\n195: - [ ] Security audit: No wildcard (*) in resources or verbs\n196: \n197: ---\n198: \n199: ## 7. References\n200: \n201: - Kubernetes RBAC Documentation: https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/\n202: - Kubernetes API Reference: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n203: - manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml ŌĆö Router RBAC template\n204: - manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml ŌĆö WorkloadManager RBAC template\n205: - manifests/charts/base/values.yaml ŌĆö RBAC configuration values\n206: - changes/AR-030/proposal.md ŌĆö Helm Chart context (RBAC as chart component)\n\n(End of file - total 206 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031 ŌĆö RBAC ķģŹńĮ« (SA/Role/Binding)\n\n## µ”éĶ┐░\n\n| Õ▒×µĆ¦ | ÕĆ╝ |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-031 |\n| Module | manifests |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (ńø«ńÜä)\n\nDefine Kubernetes RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding) for AgentCube components to enable secure, least-privilege access to Kubernetes API resources. This proposal:\n\n1. **Router RBAC**: Namespace-scoped Role for Secret management (JWT signing keys, identity secrets)\n2. **WorkloadManager RBAC**: Cluster-wide ClusterRole for sandbox lifecycle management, CRD operations, and Pod/Secret access\n3. **Helm Templating**: Parameterized RBAC creation via values.yaml flags (e.g., `router.rbac.create`)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775884934188,"end":1775884934218}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884934222,"sessionID":"ses_28502a6edffemTCed1yGL8nzbj","part":{"id":"prt_d7afd9c0a001cr9F0mq9W0Bjef","messageID":"msg_d7afd7259001PiJCuntT0qmuxP","sessionID":"ses_28502a6edffemTCed1yGL8nzbj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-5588f825fb4147f9854e02bee0fe32b8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}\n2: {{- if not .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n3: {{- fail \"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\" }}\n4: {{- end }}\n5: apiVersion: v1\n6: kind: ServiceAccount\n7: metadata:\n8:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n9:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n10:   labels:\n11:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n12: ---\n13: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n14: kind: Role\n15: metadata:\n16:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n17:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n18:   labels:\n19:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n20: rules:\n21:   - apiGroups:\n22:       - \"\"\n23:     resources:\n24:       - secrets\n25:     verbs:\n26:       - get\n27:       - list\n28:       - watch\n29:       - create\n30:       - update\n31:       - patch\n32:       - delete\n33: ---\n34: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n35: kind: RoleBinding\n36: metadata:\n37:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n38:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n39:   labels:\n40:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n41: roleRef:\n42:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n43:   kind: Role\n44:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccount