ma\n149: \n150: ```yaml\n151: # Global settings\n152: imagePullSecrets: []           # array[string] - Secret names for private registries\n153: nameOverride: \"\"               # string - Partial name override\n154: fullnameOverride: \"\"           # string - Full name override\n155: \n156: # Redis connection (must be provided by user)\n157: redis:\n158:   addr: \"\"                     # string - Redis address (host:port)\n159:   password: \"\"                 # string - Redis password (empty = no auth)\n160: \n161: # WorkloadManager configuration\n162: workloadmanager:\n163:   replicas: 1                  # int - Deployment replicas\n164:   image:\n165:     repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager\n166:     pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n167:     tag: latest\n168:   service:\n169:     type: ClusterIP\n170:     port: 8080\n171:   resources:\n172:     limits:\n173:       cpu: 500m\n174:       memory: 512Mi\n175:     requests:\n176:       cpu: 100m\n177:       memory: 128Mi\n178:   extraEnv: []                 # array[object] - Extra environment variables\n179: \n180: # Router configuration\n181: router:\n182:   replicas: 1\n183:   image:\n184:     repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router\n185:     pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n186:     tag: latest\n187:   service:\n188:     type: ClusterIP\n189:     port: 8080\n190:     targetPort: 8080\n191:   resources:\n192:     limits:\n193:       cpu: 500m\n194:       memory: 512Mi\n195:     requests:\n196:       cpu: 100m\n197:       memory: 128Mi\n198:   config: {}                   # object - Router configuration\n199:   extraEnv: []                 # array[object] - Extra environment variables\n200:   serviceAccountName: \"\"       # string - ServiceAccount name (empty = default)\n201:   rbac:\n202:     create: false              # bool - Create RBAC resources\n203: \n204: # Volcano scheduler (optional)\n205: volcano:\n206:   scheduler:\n207:     enabled: false             # bool - Enable Volcano agent scheduler\n208:     replicas: 1\n209:     image:\n210:       repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler\n211:       pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n212:       tag: latest\n213: ```\n214: \n215: ### Values Type Definitions\n216: \n217: | Path | Type | Default | Description |\n218: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n219: | `imagePullSecrets` | `array[string]` | `[]` | Secret names for private registries |\n220: | `nameOverride` | `string` | `\"\"` | Partial name override |\n221: | `fullnameOverride` | `string` | `\"\"` | Full name override |\n222: | `redis.addr` | `string` | `\"\"` | Redis address (`host:port`) |\n223: | `redis.password` | `string` | `\"\"` | Redis password |\n224: | `router.replicas` | `int` | `1` | Router deployment replicas |\n225: | `router.image.repository` | `string` | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router` | Router image repository |\n226: | `router.image.pullPolicy` | `string` | `IfNotPresent` | Image pull policy |\n227: | `router.image.tag` | `string` | `latest` | Router image tag |\n228: | `router.service.type` | `string` | `ClusterIP` | Router service type |\n229: | `router.service.port` | `int` | `8080` | Router service port |\n230: | `router.service.targetPort` | `int` | `8080` | Router container port |\n231: | `router.resources.limits.cpu` | `string` | `500m` | CPU limit |\n232: | `router.resources.limits.memory` | `string` | `512Mi` | Memory limit |\n233: | `router.resources.requests.cpu` | `string` | `100m` | CPU request |\n234: | `router.resources.requests.memory` | `string` | `128Mi` | Memory request |\n235: | `router.serviceAccountName` | `string` | `\"\"` | ServiceAccount name |\n236: | `router.rbac.create` | `bool` | `false` | Create Router RBAC |\n237: | `workloadmanager.replicas` | `int` | `1` | WorkloadManager replicas |\n238: | `workloadmanager.image.repository` | `string` | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager` | WorkloadManager image |\n239: | `workloadmanager.service.port` | `int` | `8080` | WorkloadManager service port |\n240: | `volcano.scheduler.enabled` | `bool` | `false` | Enable Volcano scheduler |\n241: \n242: ### Named Templates (_helpers.tpl)\n243: \n244: ```yaml\n245: {{- define \"agentcube.name\" -}}\n246: {{- default .Chart.Name .Values.nameOverride | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" -}}\n247: {{- end -}}\n248: \n249: {{- define \"agentcube.fullname\" -}}\n250: {{- if .Values.fullnameOverride -}}\n251: {{- .Values.fullnameOverride | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" -}}\n252: {{- else -}}\n253: {{- $name := default .Chart.Name .Values.nameOverride -}}\n254: {{- if contains $name .Release.Name -}}\n255: {{- .Release.Name | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" -}}\n256: {{- else -}}\n257: {{- printf \"%s-%s\" .Release.Name $name | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" -}}\n258: {{- end -}}\n259: {{- end -}}\n260: {{- end -}}\n261: \n262: {{- define \"agentcube.labels\" -}}\n263: app.kubernetes.io/name: {{ include \"agentcube.name\" . }}\n264: app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n265: app.kubernetes.io/version: {{ .Chart.AppVersion }}\n266: app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: {{ .Release.Service }}\n267: {{- end -}}\n268: \n269: {{- define \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" -}}\n270: app: {{ include \"agentcube.name\" . }}\n271: {{- end -}}\n272: \n273: {{- define \"agentcube.image\" -}}\n274: {{- $registry := .Values.global.imageRegistry | default \"\" -}}\n275: {{- $repository := .repository -}}\n276: {{- $tag := .tag | default \"latest\" -}}\n277: {{- if $registry -}}\n278: {{- printf \"%s/%s:%s\" $registry $repository $tag -}}\n279: {{- else -}}\n280: {{- printf \"%s:%s\" $repository $tag -}}\n281: {{- end -}}\n282: {{- end -}}\n283: ```\n284: \n285: ---\n286: \n287: ## API Contracts\n288: \n289: ### WorkloadManager Deployment Template\n290: \n291: ```yaml\n292: apiVersion: apps/v1\n293: kind: Deployment\n294: metadata:\n295:   name: workloadmanager\n296:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n297:   labels:\n298:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n299: spec:\n300:   replicas: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.replicas }}\n301:   selector:\n302:     matchLabels:\n303:       {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 6 }}\n304:       app: workloadmanager\n305:   template:\n306:     metadata:\n307:       labels:\n308:         {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 8 }}\n309:         app: workloadmanager\n310:     spec:\n311:       serviceAccountName: workloadmanager\n312:       {{- with .Values.imagePullSecrets }}\n313:       imagePullSecrets:\n314:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n315:       {{- end }}\n316:       containers:\n317:         - name: workloadmanager\n318:           image: \"{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.tag }}\"\n319:           imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy }}\n320:           ports:\n321:             - name: http\n322:               containerPort: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n323:               protocol: TCP\n324:           env:\n325:             - name: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n326:               valueFrom:\n327:                 fieldRef:\n328:                   fieldPath: metadata.namespace\n329:             - name: REDIS_PASSWORD\n330:               value: \"{{ .Values.redis.password }}\"\n331:             - name: REDIS_ADDR\n332:               value: \"{{ .Values.redis.addr }}\"\n333:             {{- with .Values.workloadmanager.extraEnv }}\n334:             {{- toYaml . | nindent 12 }}\n335:             {{- end }}\n336:           args:\n337:             - --port={{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n338:             - --runtime-class-name=\n339:           resources:\n340:             {{- toYaml .Values.workloadmanager.resources | nindent 12 }}\n341:           livenessProbe:\n342:             httpGet:\n343:               path: /health\n344:               port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n345:             initialDelaySeconds: 10\n346:             periodSeconds: 10\n347:           readinessProbe:\n348:             httpGet:\n349:               path: /health\n350:               port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n351:             initialDelaySeconds: 5\n352:             periodSeconds: 5\n353: ```\n354: \n355: ### WorkloadManager Service Template\n356: \n357: ```yaml\n358: apiVersion: v1\n359: kind: Service\n360: metadata:\n361:   name: workloadmanager\n362:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n363:   labels:\n364:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n365: spec:\n366:   type: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.type }}\n367:   ports:\n368:     - port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n369:       targetPort: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n370:       protocol: TCP\n371:       name: http\n372:   selector:\n373:     app: workloadmanager\n374: ```\n375: \n376: ### Router Deployment Template\n377: \n378: ```yaml\n379: apiVersion: apps/v1\n380: kind: Deployment\n381: metadata:\n382:   name: agentcube-router\n383:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n384:   labels:\n385:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n386: spec:\n387:   replicas: {{ .Values.router.replicas }}\n388:   selector:\n389:     matchLabels:\n390:       app: agentcube-router\n391:   template:\n392:     metadata:\n393:       labels:\n394:         app: agentcube-router\n395:     spec:\n396:       {{- if .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n397:       serviceAccountName: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n398:       {{- end }}\n399:       {{- with .Values.imagePullSecrets }}\n400:       imagePullSecrets:\n401:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n402:       {{- end }}\n403:       containers:\n404:         - name: agentcube-router\n405:           image: \"{{ .Values.router.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.router.image.tag }}\"\n406:           imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.router.image.pullPolicy }}\n407:           ports:\n408:             - name: http\n409:               containerPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n410:               protocol: TCP\n411:           env:\n412:             - name: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n413:               valueFrom:\n414:                 fieldRef:\n415:                   fieldPath: metadata.namespace\n416:             - name: REDIS_ADDR\n417:               value: \"{{ .Values.redis.addr }}\"\n418:             - name: REDIS_PASSWORD\n419:               value: \"{{ .Values.redis.password }}\"\n420:             - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n421:               value: \"http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\"\n422:             {{- with .Values.router.extraEnv }}\n423:             {{- toYaml . | nindent 12 }}\n424:             {{- end }}\n425:           args:\n426:             - --port={{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n427:             - --debug\n428:           resources:\n429:             {{- toYaml .Values.router.resources | nindent 12 }}\n430:           livenessProbe:\n431:             httpGet:\n432:               path: /health/live\n433:               port: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n434:             initialDelaySeconds: 1\n435:             periodSeconds: 2\n436:           readinessProbe:\n437:             httpGet:\n438:               path: /health/ready\n439:               port: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n440:             initialDelaySeconds: 1\n441:             periodSeconds: 2\n442: ```\n443: \n444: ### Router Service Template\n445: \n446: ```yaml\n447: apiVersion: v1\n448: kind: Service\n449: metadata:\n450:   name: agentcube-router\n451:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n452:   labels:\n453:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n454: spec:\n455:   type: {{ .Values.router.service.type }}\n456:   ports:\n457:     - port: {{ .Values.router.service.port }}\n458:       targetPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n459:       protocol: TCP\n460:       name: http\n461:   selector:\n462:     app: agentcube-router\n463: ```\n464: \n465: ---\n466: \n467: ## Error Handling\n468: \n469: ### Template Validation Errors\n470: \n471: | Error Type | Cause | Resolution |\n472: |------------|-------|------------|\n473: | `Helm lint error` | Invalid YAML syntax or missing required fields | Fix template syntax, add required fields |\n474: | `Render error` | Undefined template reference or invalid values path | Check helper template names, validate values paths |\n475: | `Missing value` | Required value not provided | Set required values in values.yaml or via `--set` |\n476: | `Invalid resource spec` | Kubernetes API schema violation | Validate against Kubernetes API schema |\n477: \n478: ### Validation Patterns\n479: \n480: ```yaml\n481: {{- if not .Values.redis.addr }}\n482: {{- fail \"redis.addr must be provided\" }}\n483: {{- end }}\n484: \n485: {{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}\n486: {{- if not .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n487: {{- fail \"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\" }}\n488: {{- end }}\n489: {{- end }}\n490: ```\n491: \n492: ### Conditional Rendering\n493: \n494: ```yaml\n495: {{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}\n496: # RBAC resources rendered\n497: {{- end }}\n498: \n499: {{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}\n500: # Volcano scheduler resources rendered\n501: {{- end }}\n502: \n503: {{- with .Values.imagePullSecrets }}\n504: imagePullSecrets:\n505:   {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n506: {{- end }}\n507: ```\n508: \n509: ---\n510: \n511: ## Testing Strategy\n512: \n513: ### Test Categories\n514: \n515: | Category | Scope | Tools |\n516: |----------|-------|-------|\n517: | Helm lint | Chart syntax validation | `helm lint manifests/charts/base` |\n518: | Template render | YAML output validation | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base` |\n519: | Values override | Custom values integration | `helm template ... -f custom-values.yaml` |\n520: | E2E deployment | Full stack deployment | `helm upgrade --install ... --wait` |\n521: | CRD validation | CRD schema compliance | `kubectl apply --dry-run=client` |\n522: \n523: ### Helm Lint Tests\n524: \n525: ```bash\n526: helm lint manifests/charts/base\n527: # Expected: 0 errors, 0 warnings\n528: ```\n529: \n530: ### Template Render Tests\n531: \n532: ```bash\n533: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n534:   --set redis.addr=\"redis.default.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n535:   --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n536:   > /tmp/rendered.yaml\n537: \n538: # Validate rendered YAML\n539: kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/rendered.yaml\n540: ```\n541: \n542: ### Values Override Tests\n543: \n544: ```yaml\n545: # test-values.yaml\n546: redis:\n547:   addr: \"redis.test.svc.cluster.local:6379\"\n548:   password: \"test-password\"\n549: router:\n550:   replicas: 2\n551:   rbac:\n552:     create: true\n553:   serviceAccountName: \"test-router-sa\"\n554: workloadmanager:\n555:   replicas: 3\n556:   extraEnv:\n557:     - name: TEST_ENV\n558:       value: \"test-value\"\n559: ```\n560: \n561: ```bash\n562: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base -f test-values.yaml\n563: ```\n564: \n565: ### E2E Integration Test\n566: \n567: ```bash\n568: helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n569:   --namespace agentcube \\\n570:   --create-namespace \\\n571:   --set redis.addr=\"redis.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n572:   --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n573:   --set workloadmanager.image.repository=\"workloadmanager\" \\\n574:   --set workloadmanager.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n575:   --set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"}]' \\\n576:   --set router.image.repository=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n577:   --set router.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n578:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n579:   --set router.serviceAccountName=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n580:   --wait\n581: ```\n582: \n583: ### Test Matrix\n584: \n585: | Test Case | Values Override | Expected Output |\n586: |-----------|-----------------|-----------------|\n587: | Default values | None | All components enabled with defaults |\n588: | Router RBAC enabled | `router.rbac.create=true` | Router RBAC resources rendered |\n589: | Volcano scheduler enabled | `volcano.scheduler.enabled=true` | Scheduler resources rendered |\n590: | Custom replicas | `router.replicas=3` | Router Deployment spec.replicas=3 |\n591: | Custom resources | `router.resources.limits.cpu=1` | CPU limit overridden |\n592: | Extra environment | `router.extraEnv=[{...}]` | Additional env vars rendered |\n593: | Image override | `router.image.tag=v1.0.0` | Custom image tag used |\n594: \n595: ---\n596: \n597: ## File Structure\n598: \n599: | Path | Role |\n600: |------|------|\n601: | `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` | Chart metadata (name, version, appVersion) |\n602: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Default configuration values |\n603: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` | Named template helpers |\n604: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` | WorkloadManager Deployment + Service |\n605: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` | Router Deployment + Service |\n606: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | WorkloadManager RBAC (SA, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding) |\n607: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Router RBAC (SA, Role, RoleBinding - conditional) |\n608: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` | Volcano scheduler (conditional) |\n609: | `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` | AgentRuntime CRD |\n610: | `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | CodeInterpreter CRD |\n611: \n612: ---\n613: \n614: ## Dependencies\n615: \n616: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n617: |---------|---------|---------|\n618: | `Helm 3` | `>=3.8.0` | Template rendering and release management |\n619: | `Kubernetes` | `>=1.24` | API versions for Deployment, Service, RBAC, CRD |\n620: | `controller-gen` | `v0.17.2` | CRD generation from Go types |\n621: | `agent-sandbox CRDs` | `v0.1.1` | Sandbox CRDs from sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox |\n622: \n623: ---\n624: \n625: ## Implementation Notes\n626: \n627: ### RBAC Rules\n628: \n629: #### WorkloadManager ClusterRole\n630: \n631: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n632: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n633: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxes` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n634: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxclaims`, `sandboxtemplates`, `sandboxwarmpools` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n635: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n636: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n637: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n638: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/finalizers` | `update` |\n639: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes` | `get,list,watch` |\n640: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes/status` | `update,patch` |\n641: | `\"\"` (core) | `pods` | `get,list,watch` |\n642: | `authentication.k8s.io` | `tokenreviews` | `create` |\n643: | `\"\"` (core) | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n644: \n645: #### Router Role (namespace-scoped)\n646: \n647: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n648: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n649: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n650: \n651: ### Health Probes\n652: \n653: | Component | Liveness Path | Readiness Path | Initial Delay | Period |\n654: |-----------|---------------|----------------|---------------|--------|\n655: | WorkloadManager | `/health` | `/health` | 10s / 5s | 10s / 5s |\n656: | Router | `/health/live` | `/health/ready` | 1s | 2s |\n657: \n658: ### Environment Variables\n659: \n660: | Variable | Source | Component |\n661: |----------|--------|-----------|\n662: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | `fieldRef: metadata.namespace` | Router, WorkloadManager |\n663: | `REDIS_ADDR` | `.Values.redis.addr` | Router, WorkloadManager |\n664: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | `.Values.redis.password` | Router, WorkloadManager |\n665: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Constructed from release namespace | Router |\n666: \n667: ### CRD Schema\n668: \n669: #### AgentRuntime CRD\n670: \n671: | Field | Type | Default | Required |\n672: |-------|------|---------|----------|\n673: | `maxSessionDuration` | string | `8h` | Yes |\n674: | `sessionTimeout` | string | `15m` | Yes |\n675: | `podTemplate` | object | - | Yes |\n676: | `targetPort` | array | - | Yes |\n677: \n678: #### CodeInterpreter CRD\n679: \n680: | Field | Type | Default | Required |\n681: |-------|------|---------|----------|\n682: | `authMode` | enum (`picod`, `none`) | `picod` | No |\n683: | `maxSessionDuration` | string | `8h` | No |\n684: | `sessionTimeout` | string | `15m` | No |\n685: | `template` | object | - | Yes |\n686: | `warmPoolSize` | int32 | - | No |\n687: \n688: ---\n689: \n690: ## References\n691: \n692: - Spec: `changes/AR-030/spec.md`\n693: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md`\n694: - Proposal: `changes/AR-030/proposal.md`\n695: - Tasks: `changes/AR-030/tasks.md`\n696: - deployment/design.md ŌĆö Reference implementation details\n697: - ci-cd/design.md ŌĆö E2E Helm usage patterns\n698: - project.md ŌĆö AgentCube project context\n699: - Helm 3 Documentation ŌĆö Chart structure, templates, values best practices\n700: - Kubernetes API Reference ŌĆö Deployment, Service, RBAC schemas\n\n(End of file - total 700 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-030 ŌĆö Helm Chart µ©ĪµØ┐õĖÄ Values Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-030 ŌĆö Helm Chart µ©ĪµØ┐õĖÄ Values |\n| Module | `manifests` |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nDefine the official Helm Chart for AgentCube deployment, providing parameterized Kubernetes manifests for all core components (workloadmanager, router, agentd, redis) with configurable values for image registry, replicas, resources, and environment-specific overrides.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/design.md","time":{"start":1775884942031,"end":1775884942043}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884942048,"sessionID":"ses_28502a6edffemTCed1yGL8nzbj","part":{"id":"prt_d7afdbaae001tVmo4yYNTpvRs3","messageID":"msg_d7afd9c9f0018J0S81R37WBqpb","sessionID":"ses_28502a6edffemTCed1yGL8nzbj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-1f1aca0d81264f2caf44063e05354efe","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-031 ŌĆö RBAC ķģŹńĮ«\n2: \n3: **Module:** `manifests`  \n4: **Language:** YAML  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define Kubernetes RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding) for AgentCube components to enable secure, least-privilege access to Kubernetes API resources. Router uses namespace-scoped Role for Secret management; WorkloadManager uses cluster-wide ClusterRole for sandbox lifecycle management and CRD operations.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Router RBAC template\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide namespace-scoped RBAC resources for Router with conditional creation and validation.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Router RBAC conditional rendering\n22: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` exists\n23: - **WHEN** `{{ .Values.router.rbac.create }}` is `true`\n24: - **THEN** ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding SHALL be rendered\n25: - **WHEN** value is `false`\n26: - **THEN** no RBAC resources SHALL be rendered for router\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: Router serviceAccountName validation guard\n29: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled (`router.rbac.create: true`)\n30: - **WHEN** `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}` is empty or not set\n31: - **THEN** template SHALL fail with error: `\"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\"`\n32: - **WHEN** value is set\n33: - **THEN** template SHALL render successfully\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount creation\n36: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n37: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is templated\n38: - **THEN** ServiceAccount SHALL have:\n39:   - `apiVersion: v1`\n40:   - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n41:   - `name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}`\n42:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n43:   - `labels` from helper template `agentcube.labels`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Router Role namespace-scoped permissions\n46: - **GIVEN** Router needs Secret access within its namespace\n47: - **WHEN** Role is templated\n48: - **THEN** Role SHALL have:\n49:   - `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`\n50:   - `kind: Role`\n51:   - `name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}`\n52:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n53:   - `rules` array with single entry:\n54:     - `apiGroups: [\"\"]` (core API group)\n55:     - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n56:     - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: Router RoleBinding binding\n59: - **GIVEN** Router Role needs binding to ServiceAccount\n60: - **WHEN** RoleBinding is templated\n61: - **THEN** RoleBinding SHALL have:\n62:   - `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`\n63:   - `kind: RoleBinding`\n64:   - `name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}`\n65:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n66:   - `labels` from helper template\n67:   - `subjects`: ServiceAccount with name from values in release namespace\n68:   - `roleRef`:\n69:     - `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n70:     - `kind: Role`\n71:     - `name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}`\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Router RBAC no cluster-wide access\n74: - **GIVEN** Router Role only grants namespace-scoped permissions\n75: - **WHEN** Role rules are evaluated\n76: - **THEN** no ClusterRole or ClusterRoleBinding SHALL be created for Router\n77: - **AND** Router SHALL NOT have access to resources in other namespaces\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ### Requirement: WorkloadManager RBAC template\n82: \n83: The system SHALL provide cluster-wide RBAC resources for WorkloadManager with full CRD operation permissions.\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ServiceAccount creation\n86: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` is rendered\n87: - **WHEN** helm template executes\n88: - **THEN** ServiceAccount SHALL have:\n89:   - `apiVersion: v1`\n90:   - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n91:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n92:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n93:   - `labels` from helper template `agentcube.labels`\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole agent-sandbox permissions\n96: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs Sandbox CRD access\n97: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for `agents.x-k8s.io` are defined\n98: - **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n99:   - `apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n100:   - `resources: [\"sandboxes\"]`\n101:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole sandbox extension permissions\n104: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs extension CRD access\n105: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` are defined\n106: - **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n107:   - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n108:   - `resources: [\"sandboxclaims\",\"sandboxtemplates\",\"sandboxwarmpools\"]`\n109:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n110:   - `resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]`\n111:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"update\",\"patch\"]`\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole CodeInterpreter permissions\n114: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs CodeInterpreter CRD access\n115: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` are defined\n116: - **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n117:   - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n118:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]`\n119:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n120:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\"]`\n121:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"update\",\"patch\"]`\n122:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]`\n123:   - `verbs: [\"update\"]`\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole AgentRuntime permissions\n126: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs AgentRuntime CRD read access\n127: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for AgentRuntime are defined\n128: - **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n129:   - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n130:   - `resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]`\n131:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\"]`\n132:   - `resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]`\n133:   - `verbs: [\"update\",\"patch\"]`\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole core resource permissions\n136: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs Pod and Secret access\n137: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for core API are defined\n138: - **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n139:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n140:   - `resources: [\"pods\"]`\n141:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\"]`\n142:   - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n143:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole TokenReview permission\n146: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs TokenReview for authentication\n147: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for authentication API are defined\n148: - **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n149:   - `apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]`\n150:   - `resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]`\n151:   - `verbs: [\"create\"]`\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding creation\n154: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager ClusterRole needs binding\n155: - **WHEN** ClusterRoleBinding is templated\n156: - **THEN** ClusterRoleBinding SHALL have:\n157:   - `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`\n158:   - `kind: ClusterRoleBinding`\n159:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n160:   - `labels` from helper template\n161:   - `subjects`:\n162:     - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n163:     - `name: workloadmanager`\n164:     - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n165:   - `roleRef`:\n166:     - `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n167:     - `kind: ClusterRole`\n168:     - `name: workloadmanager`\n169: \n170: ---\n171: \n172: ### Requirement: RBAC values.yaml configuration\n173: \n174: The system SHALL provide configurable RBAC flags in values.yaml.\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: Router RBAC create flag default\n177: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` defines router section\n178: - **WHEN** `router.rbac.create` is defined\n179: - **THEN** default value SHALL be `false` (RBAC disabled by default)\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Router serviceAccountName configuration\n182: - **GIVEN** router RBAC can be enabled\n183: - **WHEN** `router.serviceAccountName` is defined in values.yaml\n184: - **THEN** default value SHALL be `\"\"` (empty string, user must set when enabling RBAC)\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: Router RBAC enabled deployment\n187: - **GIVEN** user wants Router RBAC created by Helm\n188: - **WHEN** values.yaml is configured with:\n189:   - `router.rbac.create: true`\n190:   - `router.serviceAccountName: \"agentcube-router\"`\n191: - **THEN** Helm install SHALL create ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding\n192: - **AND** Router Deployment SHALL use `serviceAccountName: agentcube-router`\n193: \n194: #### Scenario: Router external RBAC deployment\n195: - **GIVEN** user has pre-existing ServiceAccount/RBAC externally managed\n196: - **WHEN** values.yaml is configured with:\n197:   - `router.rbac.create: false`\n198:   - `router.serviceAccountName: \"my-existing-sa\"`\n199: - **THEN** Helm install SHALL NOT create RBAC resources\n200: - **AND** Router Deployment SHALL reference existing ServiceAccount\n201: \n202: ---\n203: \n204: ### Requirement: RBAC security compliance\n205: \n206: The system SHALL follow Kubernetes RBAC best practices with minimal permission grants.\n207: \n208: #### Scenario: No wildcard permissions\n209: - **GIVEN** RBAC templates define permission rules\n210: - **WHEN** ClusterRole or Role rules are inspected\n211: - **THEN** no rule SHALL use wildcard `\"*\"` for `resources` or `verbs`\n212: - **AND** all `apiGroups`, `resources`, `verbs` SHALL be explicitly listed\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: Least privilege principle\n215: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs specific operations on resources\n216: - **WHEN** ClusterRole verbs are defined per resource\n217: - **THEN** verbs SHALL be minimum required for operation:\n218:   - Read-only resources: `get`, `list`, `watch` only\n219:   - Status subresources: `get`, `update`, `patch` only (no delete)\n220:   - Finalizers: `update` only\n221:   - Managed resources: full CRUD where lifecycle management required\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Namespace isolation for Router\n224: - **GIVEN** Router only needs secrets in its own namespace\n225: - **WHEN** Router Role is evaluated\n226: - **THEN** Role SHALL NOT grant access to cluster-wide resources\n227: - **AND** Role SHALL NOT grant access to resources in other namespaces\n228: - **AND** RoleBinding SHALL only bind within `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: TokenReview restricted to WorkloadManager\n231: - **GIVEN** TokenReview is sensitive authentication operation\n232: - **WHEN** RBAC permissions are audited\n233: - **THEN** TokenReview `create` verb SHALL only be granted to WorkloadManager\n234: - **AND** Router SHALL NOT have TokenReview permission\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ### Requirement: RBAC template validation\n239: \n240: The system SHALL provide template validation for RBAC configuration.\n241: \n242: #### Scenario: Helm template rendering validation\n243: - **GIVEN** RBAC templates are complete\n244: - **WHEN** `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router` is executed\n245: - **THEN** output SHALL contain valid YAML for:\n246:   - Router ServiceAccount\n247:   - Router Role\n248:   - Router RoleBinding\n249:   - WorkloadManager ServiceAccount\n250:   - WorkloadManager ClusterRole\n251:   - WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: Helm template failure on missing serviceAccountName\n254: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n255: - **WHEN** `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set router.rbac.create=true` is executed without `router.serviceAccountName`\n256: - **THEN** template SHALL fail with error message containing `\"router.serviceAccountName must be set\"`\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: Helm template skip when RBAC disabled\n259: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is disabled\n260: - **WHEN** `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set router.rbac.create=false` is executed\n261: - **THEN** output SHALL NOT contain Router ServiceAccount, Role, or RoleBinding\n262: - **AND** WorkloadManager RBAC SHALL still be rendered\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: Helm lint passes\n265: - **GIVEN** RBAC templates are complete\n266: - **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is executed\n267: - **THEN** lint SHALL pass with no errors related to RBAC templates\n268: \n269: ---\n270: \n271: ### Requirement: E2E RBAC validation\n272: \n273: The system SHALL validate RBAC permissions in E2E tests.\n274: \n275: #### Scenario: E2E Router secret access\n276: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is deployed with `router.rbac.create=true`\n277: - **WHEN** Router Pod attempts to create/read/update/delete Secret in its namespace\n278: - **THEN** operations SHALL succeed (permission granted by Role)\n279: - **WHEN** Router Pod attempts to access Secret in different namespace\n280: - **THEN** operation SHALL fail (namespace isolation)\n281: \n282: #### Scenario: E2E WorkloadManager sandbox creation\n283: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager RBAC is deployed\n284: - **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to create Sandbox CRD\n285: - **THEN** operation SHALL succeed (permission granted by ClusterRole)\n286: - **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to update Sandbox status\n287: - **THEN** operation SHALL succeed\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: E2E WorkloadManager CodeInterpreter lifecycle\n290: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager RBAC is deployed\n291: - **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts full lifecycle on CodeInterpreter CRD\n292: - **THEN** create, get, list, update, delete SHALL succeed\n293: - **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to update CodeInterpreter finalizers\n294: - **THEN** operation SHALL succeed\n295: \n296: #### Scenario: E2E WorkloadManager Pod read access\n297: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager RBAC is deployed\n298: - **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to get/list/watch Pods\n299: - **THEN** operations SHALL succeed\n300: - **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to create/delete Pod directly\n301: - **THEN** operation SHALL fail (only read verbs granted)\n302: \n303: ---\n304: \n305: ## Constants Summary\n306: \n307: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n308: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n309: | `ROUTER_RBAC_CREATE_DEFAULT` | `false` | `values.yaml` | Router RBAC disabled by default |\n310: | `ROUTER_SA_NAME_DEFAULT` | `\"\"` | `values.yaml` | Router ServiceAccount name must be explicitly set |\n311: | `WORKLOADMANAGER_SA_NAME` | `workloadmanager` | `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | Fixed ServiceAccount name for WorkloadManager |\n312: | `RBAC_API_VERSION` | `rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1` | RBAC templates | Stable RBAC API version |\n313: \n314: ---\n315: \n316: ## Dependencies Summary\n317: \n318: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n319: |---------|---------|---------|\n320: | `Kubernetes` | `>=1.24` | RBAC API stability (rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1) |\n321: | `Helm 3` | `>=3.8.0` | Template conditionals and validation guards |\n322: | `agent-sandbox CRDs` | `agents.x-k8s.io` | Sandbox, SandboxClaim, SandboxTemplate, SandboxWarmPool resources |\n323: | `AgentCube CRDs` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | CodeInterpreter, AgentRuntime custom resources |\n324: \n325: ---\n326: \n327: ## File Changes Summary\n328: \n329: | File | Action | Description |\n330: |------|--------|-------------|\n331: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Modified | Add validation guard for serviceAccountName requirement |\n332: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | Existing | WorkloadManager RBAC resources (no changes) |\n333: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Modified | Document `router.rbac.create` and `router.serviceAccountName` defaults |\n334: \n335: ---\n336: \n337: ## References\n338: \n339: - proposal.md ŌĆö AR-031 proposal with scope and implementation checklist\n340: - manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml ŌĆö Router RBAC template\n341: - manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml ŌĆö WorkloadManager RBAC template\n342: - Kubernetes RBAC Documentation ŌĆö https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/\n343: - changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md ŌĆö Helm Chart templates context\n344: \n345: ---\n346: \n347: ## Validation Checklist\n348: \n349: - [ ] `helm lint manifests/charts/base` passes with no errors\n350: - [ ] Router RBAC renders when `router.rbac.create=true` with valid `serviceAccountName`\n351: - [ ] Router RBAC skipped when `router.rbac.create=false`\n352: - [ ] Template fails when `router.rbac.create=true` without `serviceAccountName`\n353: - [ ] Router Role only grants Secret permissions (namespace-scoped)\n354: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole grants all required CRD permissions\n355: - [ ] No wildcard (`*`) in any RBAC resources or verbs\n356: - [ ] TokenReview only granted to WorkloadManager, not Router\n357: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding references correct ServiceAccount\n358: - [ ] E2E test: Router can manage secrets in its namespace\n359: - [ ] E2E test: WorkloadManager can create/manage Sandboxes\n360: - [ ] E2E test: WorkloadManager can create/manage CodeInterpreters\n\n(End of file - total 360 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-031 ŌĆö RBAC ķģŹńĮ«\n\n**Module:** `manifests`  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine Kubernetes RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding) for AgentCube components to enable secure, least-privilege access to Kubernetes API resources. Router uses namespace-scoped Role for Secret management; WorkloadManager uses cluster-wide ClusterRole for sandbox lifecycle management and CRD operations.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Router RBAC template\n\nThe system SHALL provide namespace-scoped RBAC resources for Router with conditional creation and validation.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775884942033,"end":1775884942046}}}}
