      Ōöé                  Ōöé         Ōöé - Sandboxes (full CRUD)          Ōöé   Ōöé\nŌöé         Ōöé                  Ōöé         Ōöé - CodeInterpreters (full CRUD)   Ōöé   Ōöé\nŌöé         Ōöé                  Ōöé         Ōöé - AgentRuntimes (read + status)  Ōöé   Ōöé\nŌöé         Ōöé                  Ōöé         Ōöé - Pods (read-only)               Ōöé   Ōöé\nŌöé         Ōöé                  Ōöé         Ōöé - Secrets (full CRUD)            Ōöé   Ōöé\nŌöé         Ōöé                  Ōöé         Ōöé - TokenReviews (create)          Ōöé   Ōöé\nŌöé         Ōöé                  Ōöé         ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś   Ōöé\nŌöé         Ōöé                  Ōöé                                                Ōöé\nŌöé         Ōöé                  Ō¢╝                                                Ōöé\nŌöé         Ōöé         ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ                                      Ōöé\nŌöé         Ōöé         Ōöé Sandbox CRDs    ŌöéŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢Č Agent Sandbox Controller         Ōöé\nŌöé         Ōöé         ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś                                      Ōöé\nŌöé         Ōöé         ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ                                      Ōöé\nŌöé         Ōöé         Ōöé AgentCube CRDs  ŌöéŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢Č WorkloadManager Reconciler        Ōöé\nŌöé         Ōöé         ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś                                      Ōöé\nŌöé         Ōöé         ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ                                      Ōöé\nŌöé         Ōöé         Ōöé Pods/Secrets    ŌöéŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢Č Kubernetes Core API               Ōöé\nŌöé         Ōöé         ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś                                      Ōöé\nŌöé         Ōöé                                                                  Ōöé\nŌöé                                                                              Ōöé\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n```\n\n### Component Relationships\n\n| Component | Scope | Resources | Purpose |\n|-----------|-------|-----------|---------|\n| Router ServiceAccount | Namespace | Pod identity | JWT signing key, identity secret access |\n| Router Role | Namespace | secrets | Manage session secrets |\n| Router RoleBinding | Namespace | SA ŌåÆ Role | Bind Router SA to Role |\n| WorkloadManager ServiceAccount | Namespace | Pod identity | CRD operations, sandbox lifecycle |\n| WorkloadManager ClusterRole | Cluster | CRDs, pods, secrets, tokenreviews | Full sandbox/interpreter management |\n| WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding | Cluster | SA ŌåÆ ClusterRole | Bind WM SA to ClusterRole |\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Router RBAC Schema\n\n#### ServiceAccount\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube\n    app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/version: {{ .Chart.AppVersion }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: {{ .Release.Service }}\n```\n\n#### Role\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: Role\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube\n    app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\nrules:\n  - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n    resources: [\"secrets\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n```\n\n#### RoleBinding\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: RoleBinding\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube\n    app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\nroleRef:\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n  kind: Role\n  name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\nsubjects:\n  - kind: ServiceAccount\n    name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n    namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n```\n\n### WorkloadManager RBAC Schema\n\n#### ServiceAccount\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: workloadmanager\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube\n    app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n```\n\n#### ClusterRole\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRole\nmetadata:\n  name: workloadmanager\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube\nrules:\n  - apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n    resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n  - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n    resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n  - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n    resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n  - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n    resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n  - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n    resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n  - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n    resources: [\"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]\n    verbs: [\"update\"]\n  - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n    resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n  - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n    resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]\n    verbs: [\"update\", \"patch\"]\n  - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n    resources: [\"pods\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n  - apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]\n    resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]\n    verbs: [\"create\"]\n  - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n    resources: [\"secrets\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n```\n\n#### ClusterRoleBinding\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRoleBinding\nmetadata:\n  name: workloadmanager\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube\nroleRef:\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n  kind: ClusterRole\n  name: workloadmanager\nsubjects:\n  - kind: ServiceAccount\n    name: workloadmanager\n    namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n```\n\n### RBAC Permission Matrix\n\n#### Router Role (Namespace-scoped)\n\n| apiGroups | Resources | Verbs | Reason |\n|-----------|-----------|-------|--------|\n| `\"\"` (core) | secrets | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete | JWT signing keys, identity secrets |\n\n#### WorkloadManager ClusterRole\n\n| apiGroups | Resources | Verbs | Reason |\n|-----------|-----------|-------|--------|\n| `agents.x-k8s.io` | sandboxes | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete | Sandbox lifecycle management |\n| `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | sandboxclaims, sandboxtemplates, sandboxwarmpools | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete | Extension CRD management |\n| `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | sandboxwarmpools/status | get, update, patch | WarmPool status updates |\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | codeinterpreters | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete | CodeInterpreter lifecycle |\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | codeinterpreters/status | get, update, patch | Status subresource updates |\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | codeinterpreters/finalizers | update | Finalizer management |\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | agentruntimes | get, list, watch | AgentRuntime read access |\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | agentruntimes/status | update, patch | Runtime status updates |\n| `\"\"` (core) | pods | get, list, watch | Pod monitoring (no create/delete) |\n| `\"\"` (core) | secrets | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete | Sandbox secrets management |\n| `authentication.k8s.io` | tokenreviews | create | Token authentication |\n\n### Values.yaml RBAC Configuration\n\n```yaml\nrouter:\n  serviceAccountName: \"\"       # Required when router.rbac.create=true\n  rbac:\n    create: false              # Default: disabled, enable for self-contained RBAC\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Router RBAC Template Contract\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `router.rbac.create` | bool | No | Default `false`. Enable to create Router RBAC |\n| `router.serviceAccountName` | string | Conditional | Required when `rbac.create=true` |\n\n### Validation Contract\n\n```\nIF router.rbac.create == true AND router.serviceAccountName == \"\"\nTHEN fail(\"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\")\n```\n\n### Router Deployment Integration\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  template:\n    spec:\n      {{- if .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n      serviceAccountName: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n      {{- end }}\n```\n\n### RBAC Rendering Contract\n\n| Condition | Rendered Resources |\n|-----------|--------------------|\n| `router.rbac.create=true` | ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding |\n| `router.rbac.create=false` | None (user provides external RBAC) |\n| WorkloadManager (always) | ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding |\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Template Validation Errors\n\n| Error | Condition | Resolution |\n|-------|-----------|------------|\n| `router.serviceAccountName must be set` | `rbac.create=true` without SA name | Set `router.serviceAccountName` in values.yaml |\n| `Helm lint error` | Invalid YAML syntax | Fix template syntax |\n| `Render error` | Undefined helper template | Verify `agentcube.labels` in `_helpers.tpl` |\n| `Missing namespace` | `{{ .Release.Namespace }}` undefined | Ensure Helm 3+ with namespace context |\n\n### Template Validation Pattern\n\n```yaml\n{{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}\n{{- if not .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n{{- fail \"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\" }}\n{{- end }}\n# RBAC resources...\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n### Kubernetes RBAC Errors\n\n| Error | Cause | Resolution |\n|-------|-------|------------|\n| `Forbidden` | Missing RBAC permission | Verify Role/ClusterRole rules |\n| `ServiceAccount not found` | SA not created | Check RBAC template rendered |\n| `RoleBinding references non-existent Role` | Role not created | Verify Role template |\n| `Cannot create cluster resource` | Namespace Role for cluster resource | Use ClusterRole for cluster-scoped resources |\n\n### Permission Denial Patterns\n\n| Scenario | Expected Behavior | Error Message |\n|----------|-------------------|---------------|\n| Router access secret in other namespace | Forbidden | `secrets \"xxx\" is forbidden: User cannot get resource \"secrets\" in API group \"\" in namespace \"other-ns\"` |\n| Router create Pod | Forbidden | `pods is forbidden: User cannot create resource \"pods\"` |\n| WorkloadManager create Pod directly | Forbidden | `pods is forbidden: User cannot create resource \"pods\"` (only read) |\n| WorkloadManager delete AgentRuntime | Forbidden | `agentruntimes is forbidden: User cannot delete` (only read) |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Test Categories\n\n| Category | Scope | Tools | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|-------|---------|\n| Helm lint | Chart syntax | `helm lint` | Validate template syntax |\n| Template render | YAML output | `helm template` | Verify RBAC resources rendered |\n| Validation guard | Conditional logic | `helm template --set` | Test fail conditions |\n| kubectl dry-run | API schema | `kubectl apply --dry-run` | Validate Kubernetes schema |\n| E2E deployment | Full stack | `helm install` | Verify RBAC grants work |\n\n### Helm Lint Test\n\n```bash\nhelm lint manifests/charts/base\n# Expected: 0 errors, 0 warnings\n```\n\n### Template Render Tests\n\n#### Test: Router RBAC enabled\n\n```bash\nhelm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n  --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n  --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router \\\n  --namespace agentcube-test | grep -A20 \"kind: ServiceAccount\"\n\n# Expected: Router ServiceAccount with name \"agentcube-router\"\n# Expected: Router Role with secrets permissions\n# Expected: Router RoleBinding binding SA to Role\n```\n\n#### Test: Router RBAC disabled\n\n```bash\nhelm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n  --set router.rbac.create=false \\\n  --namespace agentcube-test | grep \"kind: Role\"\n\n# Expected: No Router Role/RoleBinding/SA (only WorkloadManager RBAC)\n```\n\n#### Test: Validation guard\n\n```bash\nhelm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n  --set router.rbac.create=true\n\n# Expected: Error \"router.serviceAccountName must be set\"\n```\n\n### kubectl Dry-run Tests\n\n```bash\nhelm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n  --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n  --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router \\\n  --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\" \\\n  > /tmp/rendered.yaml\n\nkubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/rendered.yaml\n# Expected: No validation errors\n```\n\n### Permission Matrix Tests\n\n| Test Case | Command | Expected |\n|-----------|---------|----------|\n| Router can read secrets | `kubectl auth can-i get secrets --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:router-sa` | `yes` |\n| Router cannot read pods | `kubectl auth can-i get pods --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:router-sa` | `no` |\n| Router cannot access other ns | `kubectl auth can-i get secrets -n other-ns --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:router-sa` | `no` |\n| WorkloadManager can create sandboxes | `kubectl auth can-i create sandboxes.agents.x-k8s.io --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:workloadmanager` | `yes` |\n| WorkloadManager can create codeinterpreters | `kubectl auth can-i create codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:workloadmanager` | `yes` |\n| WorkloadManager cannot create pods | `kubectl auth can-i create pods --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:workloadmanager` | `no` |\n| WorkloadManager can create tokenreviews | `kubectl auth can-i create tokenreviews.authentication.k8s.io --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:workloadmanager` | `yes` |\n\n### Security Audit Tests\n\n```bash\n# No wildcard permissions\nhelm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n  --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n  --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router \\\n  | grep -E 'resources:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]' | grep -E 'verbs:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]'\n\n# Expected: No matches (wildcards not allowed)\n\n# No TokenReview for Router\nhelm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n  --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n  --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router \\\n  | grep -A5 \"kind: Role\" | grep tokenreviews\n\n# Expected: No matches (Router has no TokenReview permission)\n```\n\n### E2E Test Cases\n\n| Test | Setup | Verification |\n|------|-------|--------------|\n| Router secret lifecycle | Deploy with RBAC enabled | Router creates/reads/updates/deletes secrets in namespace |\n| Router namespace isolation | Deploy in ns-A, create secret in ns-B | Router access to ns-B secret fails |\n| WorkloadManager sandbox create | Deploy with RBAC | WorkloadManager creates Sandbox CRD |\n| WorkloadManager codeinterpreter lifecycle | Deploy with RBAC | WorkloadManager manages CodeInterpreter CRD |\n| WorkloadManager pod read | Deploy with RBAC | WorkloadManager lists pods, cannot create/delete |\n\n### Test Commands Summary\n\n```bash\n# 1. Helm lint\nhelm lint manifests/charts/base\n\n# 2. Render with RBAC enabled\nhelm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n  --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n  --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router \\\n  --namespace agentcube\n\n# 3. Validation guard test\nhelm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n  --set router.rbac.create=true 2>&1 | grep \"serviceAccountName must be set\"\n\n# 4. Dry-run validation\nhelm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n  --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n  --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router \\\n  | kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f -\n\n# 5. Permission audit\nkubectl auth can-i --list --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager\nkubectl auth can-i --list --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-router -n agentcube\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Router ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding (conditional) |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | WorkloadManager ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` | Named template `agentcube.labels` |\n| `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | `router.rbac.create`, `router.serviceAccountName` defaults |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` | Router Deployment (uses ServiceAccount) |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` | WorkloadManager Deployment (uses ServiceAccount) |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `Kubernetes` | `>=1.24` | RBAC API stability (rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1) |\n| `Helm 3` | `>=3.8.0` | Template conditionals, validation guards (`fail` function) |\n| `agent-sandbox CRDs` | `v0.1.1` | Sandbox, SandboxClaim, SandboxTemplate, SandboxWarmPool |\n| `AgentCube CRDs` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | CodeInterpreter, AgentRuntime custom resources |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### RBAC Scope Design\n\n| Component | Scope | Reason |\n|-----------|-------|--------|\n| Router | Namespace-scoped Role | Router only manages secrets in its namespace (JWT keys, identity) |\n| WorkloadManager | Cluster-scoped ClusterRole | Agent-sandbox CRDs are cluster-scoped; cross-namespace sandbox management |\n\n### Least Privilege Principle\n\n| Resource | Verbs | Reason |\n|----------|-------|--------|\n| pods | get, list, watch | Read-only for monitoring; WorkloadManager creates via Sandbox CRD |\n| agentruntimes | get, list, watch | Read-only reference; no direct lifecycle management |\n| agentruntimes/status | update, patch | Status updates only, no delete |\n| sandboxwarmpools/status | get, update, patch | Status subresource pattern |\n| codeinterpreters/finalizers | update | Finalizer management only |\n| tokenreviews | create | One-shot authentication; no read/delete |\n\n### Conditional RBAC Pattern\n\nRouter RBAC is optional to support:\n1. **Self-contained deployment**: `rbac.create=true` creates RBAC automatically\n2. **External RBAC management**: `rbac.create=false` with pre-existing SA for IAM integration\n\n### Namespace Isolation\n\nRouter Role is explicitly namespace-scoped:\n- Role metadata includes `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n- RoleBinding binds SA within same namespace\n- No ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding for Router\n- Router cannot access secrets in other namespaces\n\n### ServiceAccount Naming\n\n| Component | Name Source | Default |\n|-----------|-------------|---------|\n| Router | `.Values.router.serviceAccountName` | Empty (user must set) |\n| WorkloadManager | Fixed: `workloadmanager` | Always `workloadmanager` |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Spec: `changes/AR-031/spec.md`\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md`\n- Proposal: `changes/AR-031/proposal.md`\n- Tasks: `changes/AR-031/tasks.md`\n- Router RBAC Template: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n- WorkloadManager RBAC Template: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n- Helm Chart Design: `changes/AR-030/design.md`\n- Kubernetes RBAC Documentation: https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/\n- Kubernetes API Reference: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml\">\nERROR [1:3] Block collections are not allowed within flow collections\nERROR [1:5] Missing , or : between flow map items\nERROR [2:1] Unexpected flow-map-start at node end\nERROR [2:2] Unexpected flow-map-start at node end\nERROR [2:3] Unexpected seq-item-ind at node end\nERROR [2:5] Unexpected scalar at node end\nERROR [2:46] Unexpected flow-map-end token in YAML stream: \"}\"\nERROR [2:47] Unexpected flow-map-end token in YAML stream: \"}\"\nERROR [3:1] Unexpected flow-map-start token in YAML stream: \"{\"\nERROR [3:2] Unexpected flow-map-start token in YAML stream: \"{\"\nERROR [3:3] Unexpected seq-item-ind token in YAML stream: \"-\"\nERROR [3:5] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"fail \\\"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\\\"\"\nERROR [3:82] Unexpected flow-map-end token in YAML stream: \"}\"\nERROR [3:83] Unexpected flow-map-end token in YAML stream: \"}\"\nERROR [4:1] Unexpected flow-map-start token in YAML stream: \"{\"\nERROR [4:2] Unexpected flow-map-start token in YAML stream: \"{\"\nERROR [4:3] Unexpected seq-item-ind token in YAML stream: \"-\"\nERROR [4:5] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"end\"\nERROR [4:9] Unexpected flow-map-end token in YAML stream: \"}\"\nERROR [4:10] Unexpected flow-map-end token in YAML stream: \"}\"\n... and 38 more\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadma